data.title: Runaway June Singer Jennifer Wayne Marries Austin Moody In Small Florida Ceremony

data.text:
Jennifer Wayne is married!

The 38-year-old Runaway June singer, and John Wayne‘s granddaughter, tied the knot with Austin Moody over the weekend in a small, intimate ceremony, according to People.

Jennifer and Austin said their “I Dos” in front of their 20 closest friends and family in a small ceremony in Santa Rosa Beach, Florida, on Saturday, January 9.

The two held the ceremony on the beach and implemented social distancing with their wedding due to the pandemic. Jennifer actually had COVID-19 earlier in the year.

“We are taking COVID very seriously and have requested that all of the guests receive a recent COVID test before attending,” the couple shared. “We are having the ceremony outdoors with plenty of room to social distance.”

Jennifer and Austin are planning to have a big reception in Nashville when the pandemic calms down.

During the ceremony, Jennifer also wore something close to her heart – her grandmother Pilar Pallete‘s engagement ring from her grandfather, John Wayne.

“On their 10th anniversary, he matched the diamond and had it reset in a flower setting,” she shared about the story behind the ring. “Austin used his grandmother’s diamonds to create an engagement ring for me [made with help from my best friend's mom, Dobrila Pintar,] in the flower setting as well. So, I bought all of the ladies in the wedding birth month flower earrings from Local Eclectic to keep the theme.”
